Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary;
cut crosswise into 2-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating
whites from greens.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #small pot{} over
medium-high heat. Add half the ginger; cook, stirring, until fragrant,
~{1%minute}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (11⁄2 cups for 4), and
@salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook
until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, add green beans and
a splash of water; cover with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until tender,
~{1-2%minutes}. Drain.

Heat a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
@peanuts{1/2%ounce}, @sugar{1%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 4 servings), and
@water{2%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring, until water has evaporated and peanuts
are coated and lightly toasted, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wash out pan.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in pan used for peanuts over
medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce} and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{4-6%minutes}
(it'll finish cooking in the next step).

> Rinse shrimp under cold water; pat dry with paper towels. Swap in shrimp or
> beef for pork; cook, stirring frequently (no need to break up shrimp into
> pieces!), until cooked through, 4-6 minutes.

Stir green beans, scallion whites, remaining ginger, and @sugar{1%teaspoon}
(2 tsp for 4 servings) into pan with pork. Cook, scraping up any browned bits
from bottom of pan, until ginger is fragrant and pork is cooked through,
~{1-2%minutes}.

> If scallions begin to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium low.

Stir in @Szechuan paste{2%tablespoon}, @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, and
1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4). Cook, stirring, until everything is thoroughly
coated, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Turn off heat. Taste and season with salt and pepper
if desired.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with stir-fry. Sprinkle with scallion greens
and peanuts. Serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.